{"nodes":[{"pos":[32,79],"content":"Reporting tree definitions in financial reports","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Reporting tree definitions in financial reports","pos":[0,47]}]},{"pos":[93,298],"content":"This article provides information about reporting tree definitions. A reporting tree definition is a report component, or building block, that helps define the structure and hierarchy of your organization.","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"This article provides information about reporting tree definitions. A reporting tree definition is a report component, or building block, that helps define the structure and hierarchy of your organization.","pos":[0,205],"nodes":[{"content":"This article provides information about reporting tree definitions.","pos":[0,67]},{"content":"A reporting tree definition is a report component, or building block, that helps define the structure and hierarchy of your organization.","pos":[68,205]}]}]},{"pos":[832,879],"content":"Reporting tree definitions in financial reports","linkify":"Reporting tree definitions in financial reports","nodes":[{"content":"Reporting tree definitions in financial reports","pos":[0,47]}]},{"content":"This article provides information about reporting tree definitions.","pos":[881,948]},{"content":"A reporting tree definition is a report component, or building block, that helps define the structure and hierarchy of your organization.","pos":[949,1086]},{"content":"Financial reporting supports flexible reporting, so that you can easily make changes as your business structure changes.","pos":[1088,1208]},{"content":"Reports are built from various components, or building blocks.","pos":[1209,1271]},{"content":"One of these building blocks is a reporting tree definition.","pos":[1272,1332]},{"content":"A reporting tree definition helps define the structure and hierarchy of your organization.","pos":[1333,1423]},{"content":"It's a cross-dimensional hierarchical structure that is based on the dimensional relationships in your financial data.","pos":[1424,1542]},{"content":"It provides information at the reporting unit level and at a summary level for all units in the tree.","pos":[1543,1644]},{"content":"Reporting tree definitions can be combined with column definitions and report definitions, to create a building block group that can be used by multiple companies.","pos":[1645,1808]},{"content":"A reporting unit is used for each box in an organizational chart.","pos":[1809,1874]},{"content":"A reporting unit can be an individual department from the financial data, or it can be a higher-level summary unit that combines information from other reporting units.","pos":[1875,2043]},{"content":"For a report definition that includes a reporting tree, one report is generated for each reporting unit and for the summary level.","pos":[2044,2174]},{"content":"All these reports use the row and column definitions that are specified in the report definition, unless the report definition specifies that the reporting tree from the row definition should be used.","pos":[2175,2375]},{"content":"Row and column definitions are important components in the design and functionality of financial reports.","pos":[2376,2481]},{"content":"Reporting trees increase the power of the components and support flexible reporting as the business structure changes.","pos":[2482,2600]},{"content":"Financial reports that aren't based on a reporting tree use only some of the capabilities of financial reporting.","pos":[2601,2714]},{"content":"You can use multiple reporting tree definitions together with the same row and column definitions to view your organization’s data in various ways.","pos":[2715,2862]},{"pos":[2867,2896],"content":"Reporting tree best practices","linkify":"Reporting tree best practices","nodes":[{"content":"Reporting tree best practices","pos":[0,29]}]},{"content":"Before you create a reporting tree, consider the following best practices:","pos":[2897,2971]},{"content":"First determine which reporting dimensions your legal entity or company requires.","pos":[2977,3058]},{"content":"Consider how you've set up your structure, and then draw an organizational chart of your company.","pos":[3063,3160]},{"content":"The organizational chart will help you visualize how to group the reporting units into one or more reporting trees.","pos":[3161,3276]},{"content":"Start with the lowest available level of detail, such as the departments and projects that are defined in the financial data.","pos":[3281,3406]},{"content":"Add as many boxes to the level of detail as are require to show higher-level divisions or regions.","pos":[3407,3505]},{"content":"Each box represents a potential reporting unit in any reporting tree that you create.","pos":[3506,3591]},{"content":"You must also consider the best way to build your trees.","pos":[3596,3652]},{"content":"You can use an automated build process to generate a reporting tree, or you can manually create a reporting tree.","pos":[3653,3766]},{"content":"It's important that you understand both methods before you design your trees.","pos":[3767,3844]},{"content":"You can use the reporting units that are defined in your financial data system to add reporting units to the reporting tree definition.","pos":[3849,3984]},{"pos":[3989,4020],"content":"Create multiple reporting trees","linkify":"Create multiple reporting trees","nodes":[{"content":"Create multiple reporting trees","pos":[0,31]}]},{"content":"You can create an unlimited number of reporting trees to view your organization’s data in various ways.","pos":[4021,4124]},{"content":"Each reporting tree can contain any combination of departments and summary units.","pos":[4125,4206]},{"content":"A report definition can contain a link to only one reporting tree at a time.","pos":[4207,4283]},{"content":"By rearranging the structure of the reporting units, you can create different reporting trees.","pos":[4284,4378]},{"content":"You can then use the same row and column definitions for each reporting tree.","pos":[4379,4456]},{"content":"In this manner, you can quickly create different financial report layouts.","pos":[4457,4531]},{"content":"If you create multiple reporting trees, you can print a series of financial statements each month that analyze and present your company's operations in various ways.","pos":[4532,4697]},{"content":"For more information, see the examples of reporting unit structures at the end of this article.","pos":[4698,4793]},{"pos":[4798,4832],"content":"Create a reporting tree definition","linkify":"Create a reporting tree definition","nodes":[{"content":"Create a reporting tree definition","pos":[0,34]}]},{"content":"A reporting tree definition contains the columns that are described in the following table.","pos":[4833,4924]},{"content":"Reporting tree column","pos":[4928,4949]},{"content":"Description","pos":[4952,4963]},{"content":"Company","pos":[7236,7243]},{"content":"The company name for the reporting unit.","pos":[7260,7300]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">@ANY</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> value, which is typically assigned only to the summary level, enables the reporting tree to be used for all companies.","pos":[7301,7432],"source":" The **@ANY** value, which is typically assigned only to the summary level, enables the reporting tree to be used for all companies."},{"content":"All child branches have a company assigned to them.","pos":[7433,7484]},{"content":"Unit Name","pos":[8390,8399]},{"content":"The code that identifies this reporting unit in the graphical reporting tree.","pos":[8414,8491]},{"content":"Be sure to establish a unique coding system that is consistent, and that will be easy for users to understand.","pos":[8492,8602]},{"content":"Unit Description","pos":[9544,9560]},{"content":"The reporting unit title appears in the report header or footer if you enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>UnitDesc<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> as a code on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Headers and Footers<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab of the report definition.","pos":[9568,9728],"source":"The reporting unit title appears in the report header or footer if you enter **UnitDesc** as a code on the **Headers and Footers** tab of the report definition."},{"content":"The title appears in the report row description if you enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>UnitDesc<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Description<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> cell of the row definition.","pos":[9729,9853],"source":" The title appears in the report row description if you enter **UnitDesc** in the **Description** cell of the row definition."},{"content":"Dimensions","pos":[10698,10708]},{"content":"A reporting unit that draws information directly from the financial data.","pos":[10722,10795]},{"content":"It defines the logical positioning and lengths for the account and related segments.","pos":[10796,10880]},{"content":"Every reporting unit row must have a dimension in this column.","pos":[10881,10943]},{"content":"You can also put a dimension in a summary unit row (for example, for expenses that are directly related to that unit).","pos":[10944,11062]},{"content":"If you enter a dimension in a summary unit row, accounts that are used in parent units should not be used in child units.","pos":[11063,11184]},{"content":"Otherwise, amounts might be duplicated.","pos":[11185,11224]},{"content":"Row Definitions","pos":[11852,11867]},{"content":"The name of the row definition for the reporting unit.","pos":[11876,11930]},{"content":"The same row definition is used for each unit of the reporting tree.","pos":[11931,11999]},{"content":"When you generate a report, this row definition is used for each reporting unit.","pos":[12000,12080]},{"content":"The row definition can include multiple financial dimensions links.","pos":[12081,12148]},{"content":"If a row definition is specified in the reporting tree, select the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use row definition from reporting tree<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> check box on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Report<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab of the report definition.","pos":[12149,12316],"source":" If a row definition is specified in the reporting tree, select the **Use row definition from reporting tree** check box on the **Report** tab of the report definition."},{"content":"Row link","pos":[13006,13014]},{"content":"The row link to use for the reporting unit.","pos":[13030,13073]},{"content":"Row links are defined for the row definition to identify the financial dimensions to link to.","pos":[13074,13167]},{"content":"External link","pos":[14160,14173]},{"content":"The row link to use for this reporting unit.","pos":[14184,14228]},{"content":"Row links are defined for the row definition to identify the report to link to.","pos":[14229,14308]},{"content":"External file","pos":[15314,15327]},{"content":"The file path of the financial reporting worksheet to pull data from.","pos":[15338,15407]},{"content":"Page Options","pos":[16468,16480]},{"content":"This column controls whether the details for the reporting unit are suppressed when the report is viewed or printed.","pos":[16492,16608]},{"content":"Rollup %","pos":[17622,17630]},{"content":"The percentage of the reporting unit that should be allocated to the parent unit.","pos":[17646,17727]},{"content":"The percentage that you enter in this column applies to each row of the row definition before the value in the row is added to the parent report.","pos":[17728,17873]},{"content":"For example, if a child unit must be divided evenly between two departments, the amounts in each row are multiplied by 50 percent before the value is added to the department report.","pos":[17874,18055]},{"content":"One reporting unit can't have two parent units.","pos":[18056,18103]},{"content":"To allocate the amounts from a reporting unit to two parent units, create another reporting unit that has the same dimension to roll up the additional 50 percent.","pos":[18104,18266]},{"content":"Enter whole percentages without a decimal point.","pos":[18267,18315]},{"content":"For example, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>25<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> represents 25-percent allocation to the parent.","pos":[18316,18383],"source":" For example, **25** represents 25-percent allocation to the parent."},{"content":"If you include a decimal point (<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>.25<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>), 0.25 percent is allocated to the parent.","pos":[18384,18466],"source":" If you include a decimal point (**.25**), 0.25 percent is allocated to the parent."},{"content":"To use a percentage that is less than 1 percent, use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allow Rollup <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>1%<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option in the report definition.","pos":[18467,18580],"source":" To use a percentage that is less than 1 percent, use the **Allow Rollup &lt;1%** option in the report definition."},{"content":"This option is on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Additional Options<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Report Settings<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> dialog box.","pos":[18581,18668],"source":" This option is on the **Additional Options** tab in the **Report Settings** dialog box."},{"content":"You access this dialog box from the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Other<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab of the report definition.","pos":[18669,18771],"source":" You access this dialog box from the **Other** button on the **Settings** tab of the report definition."},{"content":"Unit Security","pos":[18776,18789]},{"content":"Restrictions on the users and groups that can access the information for the reporting unit.","pos":[18800,18892]},{"content":"Additional Text","pos":[19930,19945]},{"content":"Text that is included on the report.","pos":[19954,19990]},{"content":"To create a reporting tree definition, follow these steps.","pos":[21083,21141]},{"content":"Open Report Designer.","po