tiple dimensions, use wildcard characters in your dimension values.","pos":[22721,22802]},{"content":"Include/Character position","pos":[23012,23038]},{"content":"This section lists the dimensions that are defined in the financial data and shows the number of characters in the longest value that is defined for each dimension.","pos":[23047,23211]},{"content":"Select the check box for a dimension to include that dimension in the reporting tree hierarchy.","pos":[23212,23307]},{"content":"Segment hierarchy and ranges","pos":[23502,23530]},{"content":"This section shows the dimension hierarchy.","pos":[23537,23580]},{"content":"You can move the dimensions in the list to change their reporting order.","pos":[23581,23653]},{"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>From Dimension<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>To Dimension<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> fields, you can specify a range of values in each dimension.","pos":[23654,23761],"source":" In the **From Dimension** and **To Dimension** fields, you can specify a range of values in each dimension."},{"content":"If you don't specify a range, all dimension values are inserted into the reporting tree.","pos":[23762,23850]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> If you're using more than one dimension, only dimension combinations that have been posted to are returned in the results.","pos":[23851,23983],"source":"**Note:** If you're using more than one dimension, only dimension combinations that have been posted to are returned in the results."},{"pos":[23991,24198],"content":"For a screen shot that shows an example of the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Insert Reporting Units from Dimensions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box, see the \"Example of the Insert Reporting Units from Dimensions dialog box\" section later in this article.","source":"For a screen shot that shows an example of the **Insert Reporting Units from Dimensions** dialog box, see the \"Example of the Insert Reporting Units from Dimensions dialog box\" section later in this article."},{"pos":[24203,24392],"content":"To create additional segments (for example, by split one segment into two shorter segments), click the correct location in a <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Character position<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Split Segments<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","source":"To create additional segments (for example, by split one segment into two shorter segments), click the correct location in a **Character position** field, and then click **Split Segments**."},{"pos":[24397,24520],"content":"To merge two segments into one segment, click in either of the segment boxes to merge, and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Combine Segments<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","source":"To merge two segments into one segment, click in either of the segment boxes to merge, and then click **Combine Segments**."},{"content":"The hierarchy defines how dimensions report to each other and the range for each dimension.","pos":[24525,24616]},{"content":"To change the hierarchy of the dimensions, in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Segment hierarchy and ranges<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> area, select the dimension to move, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Move Up<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Move Down<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[24617,24780],"source":" To change the hierarchy of the dimensions, in the **Segment hierarchy and ranges** area, select the dimension to move, and then click **Move Up** or **Move Down**."},{"pos":[24785,24923],"content":"To specify a range of dimension values to add to the new reporting tree, in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Segment hierarchy and ranges<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> area, follow these steps:","source":"To specify a range of dimension values to add to the new reporting tree, in the **Segment hierarchy and ranges** area, follow these steps:"},{"pos":[24932,25019],"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>From Dimension<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field for that dimension, enter the first value in the range.","source":"In the **From Dimension** field for that dimension, enter the first value in the range."},{"pos":[25028,25093],"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>To Dimension<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field, enter the last value in the range.","source":"In the **To Dimension** field, enter the last value in the range."},{"pos":[25099,25188],"content":"Repeat steps 7 through 8 for each dimension in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Segment hierarchy and ranges<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> area.","source":"Repeat steps 7 through 8 for each dimension in the **Segment hierarchy and ranges** area."},{"pos":[25193,25309],"content":"After you've finished defining how your reporting units should be brought into the new reporting tree, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","source":"After you've finished defining how your reporting units should be brought into the new reporting tree, click **OK**."},{"content":"Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>File<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Save<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to save the reporting tree.","pos":[25314,25370],"source":"Click **File** &gt; **Save** to save the reporting tree."},{"content":"Enter a unique name and description for the reporting tree, and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[25371,25453],"source":" Enter a unique name and description for the reporting tree, and then click **OK**."},{"pos":[25459,25501],"content":"Open an existing reporting tree definition","linkify":"Open an existing reporting tree definition","nodes":[{"content":"Open an existing reporting tree definition","pos":[0,42]}]},{"pos":[25507,25587],"content":"In Report Designer, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Reporting Tree Definitions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the navigation pane.","source":"In Report Designer, click **Reporting Tree Definitions** in the navigation pane."},{"content":"Double-click a name in the reporting tree list to open it.","pos":[25592,25650]},{"pos":[25655,25804],"content":"To view any building blocks that are associated with the reporting tree, right-click the reporting tree definition, and then select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Associations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","source":"To view any building blocks that are associated with the reporting tree, right-click the reporting tree definition, and then select **Associations**."},{"pos":[25810,25842],"content":"Roll up data in a reporting tree","linkify":"Roll up data in a reporting tree","nodes":[{"content":"Roll up data in a reporting tree","pos":[0,32]}]},{"content":"When you use a reporting tree, you can aggregate amounts from child reporting units at the level of the parent reporting unit.","pos":[25844,25970]},{"content":"This aggregation is known as rolling up the data.","pos":[25971,26020]},{"content":"The following rules are used to roll up amounts to parent units in a reporting tree:","pos":[26021,26105]},{"content":"In a reporting tree, child units must contain dimensions, unless the reporting tree is a single-level tree.","pos":[26111,26218]},{"content":"Parent units usually don't contain dimensions in a reporting tree.","pos":[26219,26285]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> If you specify dimensions for both child units and parent units, you might cause duplication of data in the report.","pos":[26286,26411],"source":"**Note:** If you specify dimensions for both child units and parent units, you might cause duplication of data in the report."},{"content":"Reporting units that contain dimensions in the reporting tree correspond to the dimensions that are used in the row and column definitions.","pos":[26416,26555]},{"content":"The combination of dimensions determines the amounts that are returned for that unit.","pos":[26556,26641]},{"content":"For example, in example 2 later in this article, lines 6 and 7 return values only for departments 00 and 01, respectively.","pos":[26642,26764]},{"content":"The amounts for parent reporting units that don't contain dimensions in the reporting tree are determined from the child unit report and roll up the amount to the specified parent unit.","pos":[26769,26954]},{"content":"For example, if the parent unit (see Contoso USA in example 2 of data roll-up examples) has two child units (022 and 023) and doesn't contain dimensions, a report is generated for each child and the parent.","pos":[26955,27161]},{"content":"The parent total is the sum of the two child amounts.","pos":[27162,27215]},{"pos":[27221,27243],"content":"Manage reporting units","linkify":"Manage reporting units","nodes":[{"content":"Manage reporting units","pos":[0,22]}]},{"content":"Each reporting tree definition is displayed in unique views.","pos":[27245,27305]},{"content":"There is a graphical view that shows the parent/child hierarchy and a worksheet view that shows the specific information for each reporting unit.","pos":[27306,27451]},{"content":"The graphical view and the worksheet view are connected.","pos":[27452,27508]},{"content":"When you select a reporting unit in one view, it's also selected in the other view.","pos":[27509,27592]},{"content":"You can build cross-dimensional hierarchies that are based on the dimensional relationships in the financial data.","pos":[27593,27707]},{"content":"When you create a reporting tree definition, you can use the same row definitions multiple times, regardless of whether you're generating a departmental income statement or a consolidated summary income statement.","pos":[27708,27921]},{"content":"The dimensions that are defined in the row definition can be combined with dimensions in the reporting tree definition to provide various views of your organization's performance.","pos":[27922,28101]},{"pos":[28107,28131],"content":"Reporting unit structure","linkify":"Reporting unit structure","nodes":[{"content":"Reporting unit structure","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"The following types of reporting units are used in financial reporting:","pos":[28133,28204]},{"content":"A detail unit draws information directly from the financial data, from an Excel worksheet, or from another financial reporting worksheet.","pos":[28210,28347]},{"content":"A summary unit summarizes data from lower-level units.","pos":[28352,28406]},{"content":"A parent reporting unit is a summary unit that aggregates summarized information from a detail unit.","pos":[28408,28508]},{"content":"A summary unit can be both a detail unit and a summary unit.","pos":[28509,28569]},{"content":"Therefore, a summary unit can draw information from a lower-level unit, the financial data, or an Excel worksheet.","pos":[28570,28684]},{"content":"A parent unit can be the child unit of a higher-level parent unit.","pos":[28685,28751]},{"content":"A child reporting unit can be a detail unit that pulls information directly from the financial data or an Excel worksheet.","pos":[28752,28874]},{"content":"A child reporting unit can also be an intermediate summary unit.","pos":[28875,28939]},{"content":"In other words, it can be the parent unit of a lower-level unit and also the child unit of a higher-level summary unit.","pos":[28940,29059]},{"content":"In the most common scenario for reporting units, parent units have a blank cell in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Dimensions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> column, and child units have links to specific or wildcard dimension combinations.","pos":[29060,29244],"source":" In the most common scenario for reporting units, parent units have a blank cell in the **Dimensions** column, and child units have links to specific or wildcard dimension combinations."},{"pos":[29250,29274],"content":"Organize reporting units","linkify":"Organize reporting units","nodes":[{"content":"Organize reporting units","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"You can rearrange the organizational structure of a reporting tree definition by moving reporting units in the graphical view.","pos":[29276,29402]},{"content":"You can also promote reporting units to a higher level in the reporting tree or demote them to a lower level.","pos":[29403,29512]},{"content":"In Report Designer, open the reporting tree definition to modify.","pos":[29518,29583]},{"content":"In the graphical view of the reporting tree definition, select a reporting unit.","pos":[29588,29668]},{"content":"Drag the unit to a new position.","pos":[29673,29705]},{"content":"Alternatively, right-click the unit, and then select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Promote Reporting Unit<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Demote Reporting Unit<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[29706,29815],"source":" Alternatively, right-click the unit, and then select **Promote Reporting Unit** or **Demote Reporting Unit**."},{"pos":[29820,29870],"content":"Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>File<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Save<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> to save your changes.","source":"Click **File** &gt; **Save** to save your changes."},{"pos":[29876,29907],"content":"Add text about a reporting unit","linkify":"Add text about a reporting unit","nodes":[{"content":"Add text about a reporting unit","pos":[0,31]}]},{"content":"An additional text entry is a static text string of up to 255 characters that adds information to the reporting tree definition.","pos":[29909,30037]},{"content":"For example, the additional text can be a short company description.","pos":[30038,30106]},{"content":"You can create up to ten additional text entries for each reporting unit in a reporting tree definition.","pos":[30107,30211]},{"content":"The additional text appears on the report for the reporting unit that the text is assigned to.","pos":[30212,30306]},{"content":"You can add text entries from the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Description<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> column of the row definition, and from the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Headers and Footers<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab in the report definition.","pos":[30307,30453],"